# API docs sync (ER diagram + Postman)

When you add, rename, or remove **routes**, **models**, **migrations**, **resources**, or **seeders**, update both artifacts in the same change.

## Files

| Artifact | Path |
|----------|------|
| ER diagram | `docs/er-diagram.md` |
| Postman collection | `postman/Bifix API.postman_collection.json` |
| Postman environment | `postman/Local.postman_environment.json` |

Write all documentation in **English**.

## ER diagram (`docs/er-diagram.md`)

Update the Mermaid `erDiagram` when:

- A table or entity is added, renamed, or removed
- Columns or FKs change
- Relationships or cardinality change

Also update: relationships table, design notes, Laravel model/table mapping, and the endpoints table.

## Postman collection

For every new or changed endpoint, add or update a request under the matching folder:

| Folder | Routes |
|--------|--------|
| Health | `GET /api/v1/health` |
| Auth | `/api/v1/auth/*` |
| Catalog | `brands`, `bike-models`, `battery-types` |
| Bikes | `/api/v1/bikes` |
| Rides | `/api/v1/bikes/{bike}/rides` |

Each request must include:

- Method, URL (`{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/...`), and auth (Bearer / noauth)
- Description: body fields, response shape, error codes, Flutter usage note
- Example saved response when useful
- Test script to auto-set variables: `token`, `brandId`, `bikeModelId`, `bikeId`, `rideId`

If `DemoSeeder` demo data changes, sync collection description, folder notes, and example payloads.

After editing JSON: `python3 -m json.tool "postman/Bifix API.postman_collection.json" > /dev/null`

## Definition of done

Do not consider an API feature complete until:

1. Tests pass
2. `docs/er-diagram.md` reflects the schema
3. Postman has working requests for new/changed endpoints
